CatDescriptText: image published in two cropped portraits in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1957, pg. 20. Portion of accompanying article reads: "Fifth's Cook, Washington Tough Combination to Beat - When a high school team has one individual star, it isn't news. But when there are two standouts on the same ball club, as in case with Fifth Aveue, then rival teams must beware.  This season Fifth Avenue can boast of two of the strongest high school players in the city, if not the state.  Charles Cook, 6' 5" center, and Carl Washington, 6' 2" forward, have been standouts in every one of Fifth's city league games..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Fifth Avenue High School basketball team players, including number 13, Charles Cook in center, and Carl Washington on right, posed in gymnasium
